  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Pierce your <strong>red</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> a few times with a fork, then cook in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 7-8 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1686321369607-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1686321369607-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1686321369607-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1686321369607-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1686321369607-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half </strong>your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>in a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and the <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>– this is your<strong> mustard dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>and <strong>chopped tomato </strong>to the bowl with the dressing and toss – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686321592703-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686321592703-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686321592703-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686321592703-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1686321592703-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>softened potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 12-15 min or until crispy on the outside</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool and once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1686321596756-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1686321596756-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1686321596756-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1686321596756-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1686321596756-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated cheese</strong> with your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) and mix until the cheese is coated in the flour</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining wholegrain mustard </strong>to the pan with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Cook over a medium heat for 1-2 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and thickened – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p><p>Set aside the <strong>cheese sauce</strong> for later</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686321599858-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686321599858-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686321599858-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686321599858-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686321599858-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 12-15 min, remove the tray from the oven</p><p>Slice the <strong>potatoes</strong> in half down the middle (careful they will be hot!) and open them out like a book</p><p>Top each potato with 1 tsp <strong>butter</strong> and mix it through with a fork</p><p>Top with the <strong>wilted spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
